17 WHEREAS, Senator Beach's service on various other committees, including the Senate
18 Appropriations Committee, the Senate Rules Committee, and the Senate Ethics Committee,
19 further reflects his influence and leadership in shaping policy decisions that affect all parts
20 of Georgia's governance and economy; and
21 WHEREAS, Senator Beach's background outside of the Senate has been equally impressive,
22 with a successful career in business, during which he has owned and operated multiple
23 companies. He serves as the Executive Director and founder of the North Fulton
24 Improvement District (NFCID) and has held key leadership roles, including serving on the
25 boards of the Georgia Regional Transportation Authority (GRTA) and the Georgia
26 Department of Transportation as well as Chair of the Public-Private Partnership Committee
27 and the Land Development Committee; furthermore, he has served as Chairman of the Fulton
28 County Development Authority; and
29 WHEREAS, Senator Beach's integrity, approach to problem-solving, and commitment to
30 public service have earned him the respect and admiration of his colleagues and constituents,
31 as well as recognition as a strong leader in Georgia politics; and
32 WHEREAS, Senator Beach's exemplary leadership and dedication to the people of Georgia
33 were recognized on a national scale when he was appointed by President Donald J. Trump
34 to serve as the United States Treasurer, a role in which he will carry significant responsibility
35 for overseeing the nation's financial operations, managing the U.S. Mint and Fort Knox, and
36 advising on matters of fiscal policy; and
37 WHEREAS, as the first Georgian to serve in this capacity, Senator Beach will continue to
38 demonstrate the same commitment to public service, financial stewardship, and integrity that
